headline: ORLY Q3 Deep Dive: Professional Segment Drives Growth Amid Tariff-Driven Inflation and Cautious Outlook
summary: Auto parts and accessories retailer O’Reilly Automotive (NASDAQ:ORLY) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, with sales up 7.8% year on year to $4.71 billion. The company’s outlook for the full year was close to analysts’ estimates with revenue guided to $17.7 billion at the midpoint. Its GAAP profit of $0.85 per share was 2.4% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: O'Reilly (ORLY) Margin Dip Reinforces Market Caution Despite Ongoing Earnings Growth
summary: O'Reilly Automotive (ORLY) delivered annual earnings growth of 4%, with net profit margins at 14.2%, a slight dip from last year's 14.5%. Over the past five years, earnings have grown at an average rate of 6% per year, and the company expects to accelerate this to 6.5% going forward, with revenue projected to rise by 5.8% per year.
